a: append
A: append to end of line
I: insert at beginning of line

o: insert beginning of next line
O: insert beginning of previous line

^, 0: beginning of line
$: end of line
e: end of next word
w: beginning of next word
b: beginning of previous word

d: delete
p yank/copy

u: undo
U: undo line
ctrl-R: redo

r<x>: replace character
cx: replace <motion>
R: replace as you type

ctrl-G: show line information
G: end of file
<number>G: Go to line
gg: beginning of file

/: search
?: search backwards
n: next result
N: previous result
ctrl-O: O as in capital o, go back to where we came from when we originally searched.
ctrl-I: goes forward

%: find matching (, {, [

type   :s/old/new      	  replace first occurence
type   :s/old/new/g       replace occurences in line
type   :#,#s/old/new/g    where #,# are the line numbers of the range of lines where the substitution is to be done.
Type   :%s/old/new/g      to change every occurrence in the whole file.
Type   :%s/old/new/gc     to find every occurrence in the whole file, with a prompt whether to substitute or not.

:!<command> to run any external shell commands

:w <FILE> saves contents of vim file to FILE
:r <FILE>,<command> adds contents to cursor

ctrl-w ctrl-w: (yes, twice) switches vim window

ctrl-d: command completion of :

